channel.title: Incase you are intrested :)
channel.description:
[u][b]Wow my first made topic in here.[/b][/u]
Well as some know, me and a bunch of others have been working on a bot called ARGA.
It uses BCEL etc and have found it hard to actually be banned though of course there still are some detection issues we need to address and sort out.
We have now decided instead of authing and giving out free to selected members, we are going to release free, open source.
The updater wont be released of course, it is really the most important part, the part that has taken us the longest and the part that could have us fucked over if jagex gets ahold.
[b]It will be released today[/b], and i thought i'd just post for all those intrested in having a look at the source.
[b]IT HASNT YET REACHED BETA[/b]. We have also not added the PlayerManager or autologin to restrict autoing for now. We dont want all cheating communities going crazy on it just yet.
www.rs-resources.com
- Thanks

item.dc:creator: @Taios Taios
item.description:
@Taios wrote:

Quite from the 443 released.

So you can download without going to rsr, makes it easier, because its going to be a pain setting up all these accounts so i need to get an invitation mod going :).

[border]Removed Combat random Fixed Draynor fisher ( It was getting compile errors because it was using a method that wasnt provided in the source of 442, it is now provided.[/border]

Can you say a fast update?

http://www.megaupload.com/?d=KCVMGT7X

Soon as i found out of update, ARGA took 8k Mill seconds to update lol. PWNED

Out within 10 mins of runescape updating.

Thanks Geno. Just now at least people are going to know we made it. Alot of people dont tend to read credits and such. Its very disheartening when you spend this amount of time on something and others can get credit for it :), not many tend to read credits :(.
